5000|$|The first <b>World</b> <b>Food</b> <b>Conference</b> {{was held}} in Rome in 1974 by the United Nations {{under the auspices of}} the UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO), in the wake of the devastating famine in Bangladesh in the {{preceding}} two years.|$|E
25|$|The <b>World</b> Summit on <b>Food</b> Security held in Rome in 1996, {{aimed to}} renew a global {{commitment}} to the fight against hunger. The Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO) called the summit in response to widespread under-nutrition and growing concern about the capacity of agriculture to meet future <b>food</b> needs. The <b>conference</b> produced two key documents, the Rome Declaration on <b>World</b> <b>Food</b> Security and the <b>World</b> <b>Food</b> Summit Plan of Action.|$|R
